Robert A. Hawkins, fired from McDonald's, was arrested for underage drinking.
A tragic shooting at Westroads Mall in Omaha left eight dead, including Hawkins.
President Bush expressed sorrow over the incident.
Hawkins' troubled past and note hint at his motives.
Witnesses described chaos and heroism during the shooting.
The community mourns the victims and seeks answers.
The mall remains closed as investigations continue.
Hawkins' acquaintances recall a troubled but helpful young man.
The tragedy highlights the ongoing issue of gun violence in the United States.
Grief counseling is offered to those affected by the senseless violence.
